  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The data variables for insights can be the original data columns or transformed variables, while the data variables for tasks are the original data columns.",
    "For example, if the task involves analyzing vehicle weight and fuel efficiency (MPG), the task's data variables would include \"Weight in lbs\" and \"MPG\".",
    "If the insight includes a derived metric such as \"MPG per pound,\" this would be considered a transformed variable specific to the insight.",
    "The data values refer to particular values of data variables.",
    "For example, the maximum MPG value is \"48\".Visualization: Refers to the visual representation required for the task that best conveys the data and insights.visualization:= ⟨type, encoding, interaction, coordination⟩ (3) Our framework generates visualizations using Vega-Lite grammar [60], which supports the above four aspects."
  ],
